text: Agdistis parvella is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Saudi Arabia, Oman and Iran.A new species, a new synonym, and new distribution records in the genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 from Iran (Pterophoridae: Agdistinae) ==References== Category:Agdistinae Category:Moths described in 1958 Category:Moths of the Middle East Category:Insects of Iran
title: Agdistis parvella
